<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"> <channel><title>Josef&#39;s Projects</title><link>https://JosefGst.github.io/</link><atom:link href="https://JosefGst.github.io/feed_rss_created.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en</language> <pubDate>Wed, 21 May 2025 09:45:16 -0000</pubDate> <lastBuildDate>Wed, 21 May 2025 09:45:16 -0000</lastBuildDate> <ttl>1440</ttl> <generator>MkDocs RSS plugin - v1.17.1</generator> <image> <url>None</url> <title>Josef's Projects</title><link>https://JosefGst.github.io/</link> </image> <item> <title>🤖 Lingao robot ROS2</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;:robot: Lingao robot ROS2&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/JosefGst/lingao_ros2&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;gps navigation&#34; src=&#34;gifs/gps_navigation.gif&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A wannabe beach cleaning Robot but in simulation still roaming the grass. The goal is to use the coverage planner to drive up a specified area and filter big particles out of the sand, like a vacuum cleaning robot but on the beach.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://JosefGst.github.io/blog/2024/02/01/robot-lingao-robot-ros2/</link> <pubDate>Thu, 01 Feb 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://JosefGst.github.io/feed_rss_created.xml">Josef's Projects</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://JosefGst.github.io/blog/2024/02/01/robot-lingao-robot-ros2/</guid> </item> <item> <title>🔌 Power Supply</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;:electric_plug: Power Supply&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Power Supply Cabeling&#34; src=&#34;images/power_supply/power_supply_1.jpeg&#34;&gt;{ width=&#34;250&#34; }![Power Supply Cabeling](images/power_supply/...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://JosefGst.github.io/blog/2024/01/01/electric_plug-power-supply/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://JosefGst.github.io/feed_rss_created.xml">Josef's Projects</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://JosefGst.github.io/blog/2024/01/01/electric_plug-power-supply/</guid> </item> <item> <title>🚗 Autonomous RC-car race (first place) 🏆</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;:red_car: Autonomous RC-car race (first place) :trophy:&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/JosefGst/autorace&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;rc-car race&#34; src=&#34;gifs/rc_car.gif&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In this competition organized at HKUST I trained the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/NVIDIA-AI-IOT/jetracer&#34;&gt;Jetson-racer&lt;/a&gt; to drive autonomously, avoid obstacles and overtake other cars. Basically I drove along the race course and recorded images with the corresponding throttle and steering values. This data is fed into the a ML model and let it train. It was much fun and I resliced what machine learning is capable of but also it&#39;s limitations. &lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://JosefGst.github.io/blog/2021/03/01/red_car-autonomous-rc-car-race-first-place-trophy/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 01 Mar 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://JosefGst.github.io/feed_rss_created.xml">Josef's Projects</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://JosefGst.github.io/blog/2021/03/01/red_car-autonomous-rc-car-race-first-place-trophy/</guid> </item> </channel></rss>